snippet.textDisplay:
"I had metadata." If she's got the photos et c she still has it, it doesn't even have to be the original files, copies or clones are fine. You have to scrub files from metadata and it's pretty hard to get rid of all of it (it's more than dates and stuff). If she's got the files but NO metadata she either scrubbed them or can't find it. The only reason the files would be 100% clean is that she had an expert scrub them and if that's the case WELL SUIT YOURSELF, ASSHAT. Don't delete evidence you need.

...unless you realise that the metadata will show the photos to be edited or the metadata to be manipulated. In that case, sure, scrub the files, I mean, it would be pretty inconvenient to hand over files with metadata showing the photos having been taken on Amber's mobile and edited on Amber's home computer. Also: you can restore deleted files, so if you've accidentally deleted them, they can still be found.

Makes me wonder if she lost the metadata before or after Depp requested an IT-expert as one of the expert witnesses.
